---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy" description="Privacy Policy for PaperTrends - Learn how we collect, use, and protect your data." canonical="/privacy">
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
    <!-- Header Section -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-container">
        <div class="text-center mb-8">
          <h1 class="heading-primary">
            Privacy Policy
          </h1>
          <p class="text-body text-lg">
            Last updated: January 1, 2025
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Content Section -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-container">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert">
          <div class="card-elevated p-6 sm:p-8 lg:p-12">
            <h2 class="heading-secondary">About This Service</h2>
            <p class="text-body mb-6">
              PaperTrends is a free, open-source tool that provides analysis and visualization of academic research trends. We analyze publicly available data from arXiv.org and other academic sources to help researchers understand research patterns and trends.
            </p>

            <h2 class="heading-secondary">Information We Collect</h2>
            <p class="text-body mb-4">
              <strong>We do not collect personal information from users.</strong> Our service is designed to be used anonymously without requiring registration or providing personal details.
            </p>
            
            <h3 class="heading-tertiary">Minimal Technical Data</h3>
            <p class="text-body mb-4">
              The only data we may collect is basic technical information necessary for website operation:
            </p>
            <ul class="text-body mb-6">
              <li>Theme preferences (stored locally in your browser)</li>
              <li>Basic website usage statistics (anonymized)</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="heading-secondary">How We Use Information</h2>
            <p class="text-body mb-6">
              Since we do not collect personal information, there is no personal data to use. Any technical data collected is used solely to:
            </p>
            <ul class="text-body mb-6">
              <li>Remember your theme preference (light/dark mode)</li>
              <li>Improve website performance and user experience</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="heading-secondary">Data Sources</h2>
            <p class="text-body mb-6">
              Our analysis is based on publicly available academic data from:
            </p>
            <ul class="text-body mb-6">
              <li><strong>arXiv.org:</strong> Open access academic papers</li>
              <li><strong>Other Academic Sources:</strong> Publicly available research data</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-body mb-6">
              We do not collect or store personal information from these sources. All data we analyze is already publicly available.
            </p>

            <h2 class="heading-secondary">Cookies and Local Storage</h2>
            <p class="text-body mb-4">
              We use minimal cookies and local storage:
            </p>
            <ul class="text-body mb-6">
              <li><strong>Theme Preference:</strong> Stores your light/dark mode choice locally</li>
              <li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> Required for basic website functionality</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="heading-secondary">Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p class="text-body mb-4">
              Our website uses these third-party services:
            </p>
            <ul class="text-body mb-6">
              <li><strong>Google Fonts:</strong> For typography display</li>
              <li><strong>Font Awesome:</strong> For icon display</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-body mb-6">
              These services may collect their own data according to their privacy policies.
            </p>

            <h2 class="heading-secondary">Data Security</h2>
            <p class="text-body mb-6">
              Since we do not collect personal information, there is no personal data to secure. Our website uses standard security practices to protect against unauthorized access and ensure reliable service.
            </p>

            <h2 class="heading-secondary">Your Rights</h2>
            <p class="text-body mb-6">
              Since we do not collect personal information, there is no personal data to access, modify, or delete. You can clear your browser's local storage to remove any stored theme preferences.
            </p>

            <h2 class="heading-secondary">Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p class="text-body mb-6">
              We may update this Privacy Policy occasionally. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated date. Since we do not collect personal information, changes will primarily affect our technical practices.
            </p>

            <h2 class="heading-secondary">Contact Us</h2>
            <p class="text-body mb-4">
              If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices, please contact us:
            </p>
            <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="text-body mb-2">
                <strong>Email:</strong> tamara1031.hallloween@gmail.com
              </p>
              <p class="text-body mb-2">
                <strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://papertrends.otama-playground.com" class="link-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">papertrends.otama-playground.com</a>
              </p>
              <p class="text-body">
                <strong>GitHub:</strong> <a href="https://github.com/tamara1031/papertrends-frontend" class="link-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">github.com/tamara1031/papertrends-frontend</a>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Navigation -->
    <section class="section-last">
      <div class="section-container text-center">
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
          <a href="/" class="btn-primary">
            <i class="fas fa-home mr-2"></i>
            Back to Home
          </a>
          <a href="/terms" class="btn-outline">
            <i class="fas fa-file-contract mr-2"></i>
            Terms of Service
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
